turns.speaker: M
turns.content: As a matter of fact, the real cause of that row was Peter Burden.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: You knew there was nothing in that.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I knew nothing of the sort. You took presents from him.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Presents, just a trivial little broach.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Yes, I remember it well, bristling with diamonds in the worst possible taste.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: No it wasn't. It was very pretty I still have it and I wear it often.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You went out of your way to torture me over Peter Burden.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: No I didn't, you worked the whole thing up in your jealous imagination.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You must admit he was in love with you, wasn't he?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Just a little perhaps, nothing serious.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You let him kiss you; you said you did.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: What of it?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: What of it?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: It gave him a lot of pleasure, it didn't hurt me any.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: What about me?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Well, if you hadn't been so nosey and suspicious you never wouldn't have known anything about it.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: That's a nice point of view I must say.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I'm bored of this conversation.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Yes, me too, bored stiff. You want some Brandy?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: No thanks.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I have a little I think.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I don't see why you want any you've already had two glasses.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: No particular reason. Anyhow, they are very small ones.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: It just seems so silly to go on and on and on with such a thing.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You can hardly call three liquor glasses in a whole evening going on and on and on.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Well, it's become a habit with you.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You needn't be so grand just because don't happen want any yourself right now.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Don't be so stupid.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Really, Amanda.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: What?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Nothing.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: No I'm just making myself fascinating for you.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Going out somewhere, dear?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: It's a woman's job to allure the man

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: That reply has broken my heart.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: watch me a minute, will you?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: As a matter of fact, that's perfectly true.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Oh, no it isn't.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Yes it is.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Be quiet.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: It's a pity you didn't have any more Brandy it might have made you a little less disagreeable.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: It doesn't seem to work such wonders with you.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Snap, snap, snap, like a little adder.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Adders don't snap they sting.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Oh nonsense they have a little bag of venom behind their fangs and they snap.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: They sting.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: They snap.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I don't care. Do you understand? I don't care. I don't care if they bark or roll about like hoops.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Tell me, did you see much of Peter Burden after our divorce?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Yes, I did quite a lot.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I imagine you let him kiss you good deal more then.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Mind your own business.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: What riotous time you must have had.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: No restraint at all, very enjoyable, never had much anyhow.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: You're quite insufferable. I expect it's because you're drunk.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I am not in the least drunk.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I imagine, as I may have already mentioned, I've had three minute liquor glasses of Brandy the whole evening long a child of two couldn't get drunk on that.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: On the contrary a child of two could get violently drunk on only one glass of Brandy.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Oh very interesting. How about a child of four, a child of six or a child of nine?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Oh be quiet.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: We can get a good little debate going about that, don't you think? Intemperate tots.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Not very funny my dear, you better have some more Brandy.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: All right. I will.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Better turn that off I think.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Why?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Because it's late and it'll annoy the people upstairs.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: There aren't any people upstairs it's a photographer's studio.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: There are people downstairs I suppose?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: They're away in Tunis.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: This is no time of the year for Tunis.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Turn it on again, please.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I'll do no such thing.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Very well, if you insist on being boorish and idiotic.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Turn it off it's driving me mad.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: You are far too temperamental. Try to control yourself.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Turn it off.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Stop it. Stop it. I hate you.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Amanda, listen. Listen.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Listen indeed. I'm sick and tired of listening to you, damn sadistic bully.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Very amusing indeed.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Stop it. Stop it. I hate you, do you hear? You're overbearing and conceited and utterly impossible.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You're a vile tempered, loose living, wicked little beast and I hope I never see you again as long as I live.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: This is the end, do you hear? The end finally and forever.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You're not going like this.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Oh yes I am.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You're not.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Yes, I am. Let go of me you're cruel fiend and I hate and loathe you. Thank God I realized who you really are before I would ever, ever marry you again. I would never marry you again. I'd rather die in torment.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Shut up.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Shut up.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I wouldn't marry you again if you came to me on your bended knees. You're a evil minded little vampire. I hope to God I never see you again as long as I live.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: You're a beast. I hate you. Stop it. Stop it.
